# Executive Overview

BOEING 220-G GLOBAL represents the convergence of multiple PI220 aerospace programs into a single distributed-lift autonomous aerospace platform.

The architecture combines:

* STARFRAME SF-1 structural intelligence lattice
* AFAT-X10V2 adaptive aerodynamic systems
* NEO CORE NODE recursive governance
* NEO Turbine hybrid propulsion ecosystem
* X2M predictive flight intelligence
* Global telecommunications infrastructure

The objective is the creation of an ultra-endurance aircraft capable of functioning simultaneously as:

* Telecommunications node
* Surveillance platform
* Atmospheric research station
* Persistent logistics relay
* Strategic command asset
* Aerospace experimentation platform

Unlike conventional aircraft which concentrate lift and propulsion in limited zones, BOEING 220-G distributes aerodynamic, structural, thermal and propulsion responsibilities across the entire vehicle architecture.

